### Labeled switch §

When a switch statement is labeled, it can be referenced from a `break` or `continue` . `break` will return a value from the `switch` .

A `continue` targeting a switch must have an
operand. When executed, it will jump to the matching prong, as if the `switch` were executed again with the `continue` 's operand replacing the initial switch value.

